# -*- mode: conf -*-

### Default bindings

clear
ctrl+semicolon start
Escape end
ctrl+bracketleft end
q record ~/.keynav_macros
shift+at playback
a history-back
h cut-left
j cut-down
k cut-up
l cut-right
shift+h move-left
shift+j move-down
shift+k move-up
shift+l move-right
space warp,click 1,end
Return warp,click 1,end
semicolon warp,end
w warp
## "windowzoom" makes keynav crash in clfswm.  Disable it.
#t windowzoom
c cursorzoom 300 300
e end
1 click 1
2 click 2
3 click 3
ctrl+h cut-left
ctrl+j cut-down
ctrl+k cut-up
ctrl+l cut-right
y cut-left,cut-up
u cut-right,cut-up
b cut-left,cut-down
n cut-right,cut-down
shift+y move-left,move-up
shift+u move-right,move-up
shift+b move-left,move-down
shift+n move-right,move-down
ctrl+y cut-left,cut-up
ctrl+u cut-right,cut-up
ctrl+b cut-left,cut-down
ctrl+n cut-right,cut-down


### User bindings

## For one hand using
# If we start keynav with binding `ctrl+grave`, keynav will crash and X will
# report a message like this:
#
#     X Error of failed request:  BadAccess (attempt to access private resource denied)
#       Major opcode of failed request:  33 (X_GrabKey)
#       Serial number of failed request:  25
#       Current serial number in output stream:  33
#
# It seems that a certain process is grabbing `ctrl+grave`, so don't bind it.
#
# ctrl+grave start
ctrl+alt+z start

## Dragging.  Likewise, 1 is the left button.
4 drag 1
5 drag 2
6 drag 3
alt+4 drag 1 alt
shift+4 drag 1 shift
shift+alt+4 drag 1 shift+alt
### Dragging for libvte-based terminal emulators.
ctrl+shift+4 drag 1 ctrl+shift
ctrl+shift+h move-left
ctrl+shift+j move-down
ctrl+shift+k move-up
ctrl+shift+l move-right

## Enable arrow keys.
Left cut-left
Down cut-down
Up cut-up
Right cut-right
shift+Left move-left
shift+Down move-down
shift+Up move-up
shift+Right move-right

ctrl+g end

ctrl+alt+r restart
ctrl+alt+x quit
daemonize
